post_text:
Pep Rally Friday, September 18th

Due to COVID 19 safety measures, parents and community members must adhere to regulations set in place.

Each campus will have their own pep rally. Elementary and Middle School pep rallies will be student and staff attendees only. Please do not pick up any students early in order for them to attend the high school pep rally. Adhere to the normal pick up routine.

Parents and community members are welcome to attend the High school pep rally only from 3:10 to 3:25 located in the High School Gym. You must check in through the High school front office, go directly to the gym and sit in the designated parent section. Face masks are required.

GISD is attempting to maintain minimal contact between the campuses.

Thank you for your cooperation, so the students can enjoy a pep rally.

ATTENTION GARRISON FFA EXHIBITORS:

The plan for Pineywoods Fair 2020 is to go forth as normal validation will be on June 20th. You as the exhibitor will have to sign a form that says you understand the fair could not happen due to unknowing circumstances going forth with COVID-19. Please let us know if you are considering showing an animal at the Pineywoods Fair. Do not hesitate to contact us by phone or email if you have any questions or concerns.

Please submit your Garrison FFA Exhibitor Form with the $20 Exhibitor Membership Fee to the Garrison Ag Science Department OR you may bring to validation on June 20th. These exhibitor forms can be found on the Garrison ISD website —> Links —> Extracurricular —> FFA. If you would like a form emailed directly to You, please let us know.

post_text:
Garrison ISD Family,

On Monday October 21 at approximately 8:10 we received word of a chemical spill that could possibly contain hazardous material. The spill occurred approximately 3 miles south of the GISD campus and the wind was out of the North. We alerted staff members to review evacuation procedures from the crisis prevention plan. Appropriate personnel were notified and had buses in place for a planned evacuation of GISD. In conjunction with the Nacogdoches County Emergency Management Team it was determined that GISD was outside of the ¼ to ½ mile evacuation radius. It was recommended for GISD to observe a shelter in place/hold for the remainder of the school day. Buses will run at 3:25 with alternate routes and small expected delays for students that ride buses #2 and #7. We would like to thank the GISD family for their patience and cooperation during this process to ensure the safety for the students at GISD.

Reid Spivey
Superintendent
Garrison ISD

Parents, please remember:

If you want your child to be given medication of any kind, you MUST send the medication for them to take. The school DOES NOT keep medications in the Nurse Office for students to take unless it is their own medication provided by their parent/guardian for use at school.

All medications (Prescription and/or over the counter medications) must be in the original containers with the most recent dates/information on the bottles. Expired medications will not be administered.

Medication administration forms have been sent home with students during the past week; your student must have one of these completed every school year in order to receive medications while at school.

Thank you,
Mrs. Teri McFadden
School Nurse

post_text:
On Saturday, June 15, we learned of the passing of a 12th grade Garrison High School student, Brandon Tenison.

We are shocked and saddened by the news of this tragic event. Our hearts are hurting for this family and friends at this time. We have made counselors available beginning tomorrow at Garrison ISD for anyone in our school community. These counselors will remain in place as long as needed to help support our students and staff through this difficult time.

We ask that you continue to show the family of Brandon Tenison the love and support of our school and community. This event is tragic for the community and even more so for the students and staff that cared so for Brandon.

Please continue to keep the family of Brandon Tenison in your thoughts and prayers.

In case you have not heard, here are the results from the Region III Golf Championship this week at Pine Dunes Resort & Golf Club in Frankston.

Team Division
Tristan Adkison: 91 (178)
Andrew Nichols: 93 (200)
Drew Wise: 106 (222)
Blake Greer: 117 (241)
Wesley Stanley: 120 (232)

Two-day team total: 829 for a 7th place finish overall

Medalist Division
Kaleb Bradford: 133 (258)

(Two-day total)

Adkison's 178 qualifies him for the UIL State Golf Championship to be held May 20 & 21 at Roy Kizer Municipal Golf Course in Austin.

Thanks to everyone who helped with the treat bags for the guys ahead of this week's tournament. We appreciate your support of Bulldog Golf and Garrison High School's athletic programs.

Coach Greg Rowe

Last night at the Garrison vs. Woden basketball game our students exhibited unsportsmanlike behavior at various times during the varsity boys game. Although the intent of our fans was to support the Bulldogs and help cheer them to victory, their actions resulted in a negative connotation toward the Woden players and their fans. GISD regrets the incident and has addressed the unsportsmanlike behavior with those involved. Our expectations have always been, and will continue to be, for our students, parents, employees, and fans to support our teams and players in a positive manner and remain respectful toward our opponent.

Sincerely,

Arnie Kelley
Interim Superintendent
Garrison ISD

kelleya@garrisonisd.com

post_text:
UIL Region III Cross Country Championships

What turned out to be a perfect day for racing, also turned into a gritty and tough battle for the chance to compete at the state meet for Jaiyah Hodge. Racing against the toughest runners in the region, and battling through the water- saturated and muddy course, Jaiyah put down a new personal best of 13:57 (old PB was 14:03). She raced like a champion, consistently moving up throughout the entire race, never giving up. Jaiyah put together her best race of the season. Unfortunately, Jaiyah fell short of qualifying for the State Championships by 1 place. It is a bittersweet day for Jaiyah but an amazing close to a wonderful season. If you see her please congratulate Jaiyah on her awesome 2018 cross country season!

Coach Guerra

If payment is submitted by October 1, students will receive a Free T-shirt along with the numerous opportunities offered through the FFA Organization.

FFA Membership forms are available for students in the 8th-12th Grade at the Garrison Ag Department.

post_text:
Results from Texas FFA State Degree Check:

Please congratulate Payton Ramsey, as she was selected to receive a renewable $20,000 Texas FFA Scholarship from the Houston Livestock Show & Rodeo. Payton's hardwork and dedication to her SAE projects and FFA career has earned her top honors towards this award.

Also, please send another big congratulations to our Texas FFA State Proficiency Award Winners - Hope Piazza & Mallory Moore.

Hope and Mallory will both receive a $1,000.00 scholarship for being named a state winner in their Proficiency categories!

Garrison FFA is also receiving a GOLD rating on their Golden Horizon Award. Garrison FFA ranked as the 8th overall chapter in the state of Texas in the Division II, Multi-Teacher category.

Our student's accomplishments will be honored at the 90th annual Texas FFA State Convention in Fort Worth this July.

Danni Lunsford Amos
Garrison FFA

post_text:
YOU ARE INVITED!

Mrs. Kimbrough's 8th grade ELA class will present their USO Show and World War II / Holocaust Museum on Tuesday, May 29 during two performances, 1 P.M. and 6:30 P.M. in the Garrison Middle School gym. ALL VETERANS WILL BE OUR SPECIAL GUESTS and will be recognized. If you know a World War II veteran, please give him/her an extra special invitation. IF YOUR RELATIVE OR FRIEND WAS A WWII VET AND HAS PASSED ON, please share a picture with us for our Table of Honor which will be displayed as a memorial to the Greatest Generation.

The students would appreciate your attendance and support!

Rabbit Exhibitors,

Remember that your $50.00 deposit towards your pen of PWF Market Rabbits is due THIS FRIDAY, MAY 25, to the Garrison Ag Department. When you submit your deposit, please let us know how many rabbits you would like to order and include the exhibitor's name with your order as well.

Each rabbit is $50.00/head.

Also, keep in mind that we encourage ordering at least 5 rabbits/exhibitor.

Please make checks payable to Heaton Rabbits.

If you have any questions, please contact the Garrison Ag Department (936) 347-7034.

Danni Lunsford Amos
Garrison FFA

post_text:
Congratulations to our Garrison Entomology team on an awesome CDE Season!

Extremely proud to say we fell one point short of the tie breaker for 10th place Team at the state contest. However, with two rookies and two veteran freshmen, no one is complaining about finishing the season as 11th in the state. 😉

Talon Wright - 12th High Individual

Mallory Moore - 33rd Individual

Madison Chanowski - 67th Individual

Jessica Box - 79th Individual

There were over 150 Entomology teams with 600+ individuals that competed in the CDE Contest this year.

Please congratulate these students on finishing 11th overall with their individual ranks as mentioned.....a HUGE accomplishment to wrap up the end of the year!

Last week, the Garrison ISD Veterinary Medicine Applications Class took an educational visit, touring the Nacogdoches County Animal Shelter.

While we were there, students received a private tour of the facility, learned about proper animal health, care and handeling techniques as well as administered friendly one on one interaction with the canines and felines of the county.

Students in attendance:

Kolby Townsend
Casey Box
Faith Crump
Makayla Hamilton
Lexi Johnson
Graysie Smith
Jaci Hudman

Thank you for allowing our students this opportunity to further advance their educational goals.
